Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Remove the @Filo Pastry Sheets{1/2} from the fridge and
bring it to room temperature. Remove the pastry from the packet and lay flat on the
counter, covered with a damp #tea towel{}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in a
large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the oil is hot, add the
@Diced Chicken Thigh{260%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until golden
brown on the outside, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging. The chicken
> is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, fill and boil your #kettle{}. Trim the root and the dark green leafy part
from the @Leek{1}. Halve lengthways then thinly slice. Peel and grate the
@Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @Carrot{1} then quarter
lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways into small pieces.

Add the leek and carrot to the chicken and stir-fry until the leek has softened,
~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Add the
@Plain Flour{1%tbsp} and cook, stirring, until no lumps remain, ~{1-2%minutes}. Pour
the boiling @Water for the Stock{200%ml} into a #jug{}, then stir in the
@Chicken Stock Paste{15%g}. Gradually pour the stock into pan, stirring continuously.
Bring to a simmer, then stir in the @Creme Fraiche{75%g} and cook until thickened,
~{4-5%minutes}.

While the sauce simmers, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{45%g}. Drain the
@Sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}. Remove the frying pan with the filling from the
heat and stir through the sweetcorn and cheese. Season to taste with salt and
pepper, then transfer to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Halve the filo pastry sheets to make squares. Scrunch each sheet into a very loose
ball and place on top of the filling. Repeat until the whole pie is covered, making
sure not to overcrowd the pastry. Drizzle the whole thing with @oil{a drizzle}, and
then bake on the top shelf of your oven until the filo is golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Divide the chicken pot scrunch pie between your #bowls{} and dig in. Enjoy!